![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/6dda955f-af13-408a-8324-213b2d0379b7/ep309.jpg?format=original)

The Killer is the latest movie from auteur director David Fincher. Based on the French graphic novel by Alexis "Matz" Nolent and Luc Jacamon, the film stars Michael Fassbender as a methodical and no-nonsense assassin who finds himself in deep water after a botched hit. Join us as we review this film, talk about its themes, and debate whether the accident is even an accident at all in this slightly green-tinted episode of the Major Issues Podcast!  
  
Please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us wherever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by **ComicBook Clique**, the only stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.  

